As Jira and Confluence become more tightly integrated, project managers want to see as much information as possible without actually having to go to Jira.  What would be helpful is if the 'links' in a jira issue could be displayed in a new column of the jira issue macro.

The specific benefit of this is that if a Jira issue has a link to a page in Confluence, a user viewing the jira case in Confluence would not need to navigate to Jira to find this other page the issue is linked to.  Instead, they could see the link(s) in Confluence and navigate straight to the other pages related to the ticket without leaving Confluence.

