If a Popular Labels Macro Heatmap exists in a footer for the page layout, the font sizes for the text labels are being overridden in 5.1.3.0  

Sounds very similar (if not the exact same issue) as https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-25201?jql=text%20~%20%22popular%20label%20footer%22. 


Steps to reproduce:
1. Create or edit a page, select a page layout that has a footer section (doesn't matter which one) 
2. Insert the Popular Labels Macro into the footer section of the page layout, choosing to display as a heatmap.
3. Save and view the page.

The HTML formatting for the labels still exists, but are being overridden by :

#main .wiki-content .footer p, #main .wiki-content .footer a { 
    font-family: arial,sans-serif; 
    font-size: 14px; 
}

